Comment_contributor: In the expression for two to four, lokuang which may be omitted, appears to mean ‘bone (of the finger)’
lu means ‘two’ in many Austronesian languages.
In the expression for two to four, lokuang which may be omitted, appears to mean ‘bone (of the finger)’
bungte refers to ‘one whole (person)’ although the word for man is not the same.
